-- Standard Chartered Kenya Profit Rises on Loan Income
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-11-02T12:03:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/standard-chartered-kenya-nine-month-net-rises-on-loan-income.html
Standard Chartered Plc ’s Kenyan unit,
the East African nation’s third-biggest lender by market value,
said nine-month profit rose 16 percent as income from loans
increased.  Net income climbed to 4.3 billion shillings ($53.29
million) in the period through September, from 3.7 billion
shillings a year earlier,  Standard Chartered Bank Kenya Ltd. 
said in a statement e-mailed by the Nairobi Stock Exchange
today. Net interest income, the money banks make from issuing
loans, grew 11 percent to 6.1 billion shillings, according to
the statement.  The bank’s board recommended an interim dividend of 5
shillings, payable on or after Dec. 20, it said.  Shares Standard Chartered Kenya fell 9 shillings, or 3.2
percent, to 270 shillings at 12:23 p.m. in Nairobi. The stock
has risen 71 percent so far this year, outperforming a 44
percent advance by the benchmark  NSE-20 Index  over the same
period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
